BT /F2 13.5 Tf 72 387 Td (1. Background and aim) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 366 Td (Official labor statistics confirm AI-driven displacement only after a lag of quarters. By then the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 351.2 Td (exposed households have already absorbed the financial stress. We ask whether a combined) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 336.4 Td (AI-exposure and household financial-stress search signal leads realized occupational) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 321.6 Td (unemployment by one to three months, among the most exposed occupations, across US states,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 306.8 Td (in the generative-AI period. This is a measurement and prediction study, not a causal one. We) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 292 Td (never claim AI caused any specific household's distress.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.5 Tf 72 259.2 Td (2. Data-access statement \(why we register now\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 238.2 Td (As of registration we have built, or will build, only the inputs: the exposure composite and the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 223.4 Td (search signal. We have not accessed, pulled, summarized, or inspected the outcome series) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 208.6 Td (\(CPS occupational unemployment\) for the test window. We post this design first, then pull the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 193.8 Td (outcome. That ordering is the credibility claim, so we state it plainly and date it.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.5 Tf 72 161 Td (3. Hypotheses) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 140 Td (-   H1 \(confirmatory, primary\). The combined AI-distress signal at month t is positively related) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 125.5 Td (    to realized occupational unemployment at t+k, for k of 1, 2 and 3 months, among) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 111 Td (    high-exposure occupations \(top tercile of the exposure composite\). Operationally, the sum of) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 96.5 Td (    the distributed-lead coefficients over k is positive at the threshold in section 6.) Tj ET
endstream
