BT /F1 11 Tf 72 676.5 Td (    substitution-coded terms do.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.5 Tf 72 644 Td (4. Variables) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.5 Tf 72 615 Td (4.1 Predictor: the combined AI-distress signal) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 597 Td (Two pieces, an exposure layer and a search layer.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 577.2 Td (Exposure composite. For each SOC-coded occupation we build a composite from three) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 562.4 Td (published indices: Felten, Raj and Seamans \(AIOE, 2021\); Eloundou, Manning, Mishkin and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 547.6 Td (Rock \(GPT exposure, 2023\); and Brynjolfsson, Mitchell and Rock \(suitability for machine) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 532.8 Td (learning, 2018\), where available. Each index is z-scored across occupations, then averaged) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 518 Td (with equal weights by default. We roll the occupation scores up to states with BLS OEWS state) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 503.2 Td (employment shares:) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.7551 Tf 78 480.4 Td (AIExposure_state = sum over occ of \( employment_share[state, occ] x ExposureScore[occ] \)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 465.931 Td (The high-exposure group is the top tercile of the composite, employment-weighted across) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 451.131 Td (detailed occupations. The low-exposure group is the bottom tercile, used as the H2 placebo. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 436.331 Td (confirmatory test \(H1, H2\) runs on these two groups.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 416.531 Td (Occupation clusters \(the descriptive layer\). For the public cube and for the secondary by-cluster) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 401.731 Td (breakout we use six SOC major groups, chosen because their exposure varies widely:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 381.931 Td (1.  Office and administrative support \(SOC 43\), high exposure) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 367.431 Td (2.  Computer and mathematical \(SOC 15\), mixed) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 352.931 Td (3.  Healthcare practitioners \(SOC 29\), low to moderate) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 338.431 Td (4.  Production \(SOC 51\), moderate) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 323.931 Td (5.  Transportation and material moving \(SOC 53\), moderate) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 309.431 Td (6.  Education, training and library \(SOC 25\), moderate) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 289.931 Td (Search layer. We pull Google Health Trends volumes for an AI-distress ontology in four) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 275.131 Td (categories:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 255.331 Td (-   Displacement awareness: "will AI take my job", "AI replaced me", "job to AI") Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 240.831 Td (-   Reskilling intent: "reskill from [occupation]", "career change at 40", "learn to code 2026") Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 226.331 Td (-   Acute distress: "laid off tech", "severance negotiation", "unemployment after layoff") Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 211.831 Td (-   Adaptation, tracked separately as augmentation rather than substitution: "use ChatGPT at) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 197.331 Td (    work", "AI tools for [occupation]") Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 177.831 Td (Each term passes a signal-to-noise screen before it goes live. We normalize each series as) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 163.031 Td (divergence from a trailing 52-week baseline, with robustness at 26 and 104 weeks, and we pull) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 148.231 Td (from January 2022 so the divergence is defined from the first test month. Google Health Trends) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 133.431 Td (is geographic \(state by week\), so the search layer is measured at the state level; the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 118.631 Td (occupational content of the test comes from stratifying the outcome by exposure.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.5 Tf 72 90.8306 Td (4.2 Outcome) Tj ET
endstream
